 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.12","title":"robot-redesign/validation: add audit-trail and actor-attribution verification coverage","description":"Add dedicated verification for auditability and actor attribution so the redesign can prove operator-state changes, actuation loops, incident transitions, and disclosure decisions remain traceable across restart, replay, and transport boundaries.","design":"The tests should cover contract examples for actor-attributed attention-state changes, actuation request and outcome trails, incident lifecycle history, audit visibility in diagnostics or inspect flows, and the interaction between sensitivity redaction and audit usefulness. Coverage should include package-local unit tests for store APIs and event shaping, SQLite or restart integration tests for retention and replay behavior, Go-based e2e scenarios where multiple actors or sessions mutate state, and benchmark or regression checks that audit capture does not make hot paths noisy or expensive. Logging should be excellent: actor identifiers, origin classes, request IDs, affected references, timestamps, decision reasons, disclosure states, replay mode, and diffs that explain missing or malformed audit history.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when automated coverage proves that audit-worthy events are persisted and exposed consistently enough that a maintainer can answer who changed this, what request caused this effect, and why this disclosure or override happened, with detailed logs when any part of that trail breaks.","notes":"Auditability is a product feature here, not compliance theater. If a failure can erase or obscure operator trust history without a focused failing test, this task is incomplete.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-22T01:56:56.309450111Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T16:43:09.985831755Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T16:43:09.985369821Z","close_reason":"Verified implemented. 